name: deep well closure, for geothermal power, onshore, 6000m | deep well closure | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8260/documentation

This dataset represents the closure of a borehole of 6000 m depth for geothermal power generation in an unspecific rock formation. A usage duration of 20 years is estimated, after which the well is filled with cement and gravel and sealed with a concrete slab.

This is a service for closure of disused deep onshore wells.

This activity ends with the closed and sealed well.

This dataset includes the materials needed for the closure. No energy is needed for the filling, only transports accounted for in the corresponding market datasets.

This dataset doesn't include recuperation of the land used.
category: B:Mining and quarrying/09:Mining support service activities/099:Support activities for other mining and quarrying/0990:Support activities for other mining and quarrying

processDocumentation.timeDescription: The exchanges in this dataset have a lifetime assigned of 20 years. Thus they are only taken from the market in 20 years, not today.
